<p>My ionic app requires users current location. So the first time the user installs the app normally there is a permission window prompts with some message and Allow/Don't allow options (iOS here).  Is there a way in Ionic to check if the user actually allowed the app to use his/her location ? In other words the check whether he/she pressed Allow or Don't Allow ?</p>  <p>This is how am I using Cordova Geolocation plugin in my Ionic App to get the users location:</p>  <pre><code>.service('LocationService', function($cordovaGeolocation,$q) {         return {              getLocation: function(){                  var coordinates = $q.defer();                 $cordovaGeolocation.getCurrentPosition().then(function (position) {                           coordinates.resolve({                             latitude: position.coords.latitude,                             longitude: position.coords.longitude                         })                  });                  return coordinates;              }         }     }) </code></pre>